    "long_instructions": "The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Store</code> class has an instance variable <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">inventory</code> that represents a list of <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Item</code> objects.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">Store</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">findMostExpensive()</code> method that returns the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">Item</code> in the inventory with the highest price.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">StoreRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">findMostExpensive()</code> method and print the result.",
